name: SOLAR ECLIPSE - A
description:
I have 2 rooms to rent for the solar eclipse on August 21, 2017. (one room has been rented, the other is still available)

NOTE: I AM RENTING EACH ROOM SEPARATELY - THIS PRICE IS PER ROOM. $175 PER NIGHT PER ROOM - 2 NIGHT MINIMUM PER ROOM.

Private room - queen bed - nicely decorated and comfortable. Bathroom is at the end of the hall.

MUST love animals as I currently have 1 big dog and a 2 cats

The space
Both rooms are very nice with a queen beds - house has central A/C and the house is clean and spacious. Both guest rooms will sleep 2 comfortably

NOTE: I AM RENTING EACH ROOM SEPARATELY - THIS PRICE IS PER ROOM. $175 PER NIGHT PER ROOM - 2 NIGHT MINIMUM PER ROOM.

This is for the lunar eclipse in August 2017

Guest access
Guests will have access to the kitchen, family room, living room and dining room. As well as a beautiful deck and hot tub. There is a new HDTV in the guests
neighborhood_overview: House is on a quiet cul de sac in a lovely neighborhood on top of a hill.  Views off the deck are facing north and you can see the hills and trees - sometimes I think I can see Portland :-).  It is very quiet and peaceful.
host_about:
Hi - I have been retired for two years and am enjoying life.  I live with my fur kids - Duncan, a lovable flat coated retriever and  1 cat.  I have a lovely home where you can enjoy the deck, the yard and the hot tub.  I live on top of a hill with lovely views.  

I will be at home when you are here and you are welcome to join me in the family to watch TV, read a book or chat.  You are also welcome to use the kitchen, please ask for assistance.  I have a Keurig for those of you that drink coffee - I enjoy my morning cup.

Looking forward to making some new friends.

Thank you,
Roberta

name: Quiet and cozy home in South Salem.
description:
This cozy, tidy, and well kept home is located in the south Salem hills away from the hustle and bustle. The home is easily accessible to the downtown area, close to shops, parks, restaurants. Enjoy the quiet, trees, birds, on two private decks.

The space
My home is nestled in a wooded area within the city limits, however, the setting is rural and quiet. Guests have a private bedroom and bathroom. The large windows throughout the home provide natural light with excellent views of nature and outdoor critters.

Guest access
Guests have access to the main living area, kitchen, laundry, private bedroom and bathroom, large closet, two decks, and Wifi.
neighborhood_overview: I live in a great neighborhood and have been here for about 30 years.  I love the outdoor area as well as my close proximity to the main downtown area.  Downtown Salem has many locally owned restaurants and night spots.  I am also very close to Willamette University.  Guests will experience a unique, clean, quiet, and welcoming area in Salem.
host_about:
I have lived in my home in South Salem for 30 years.  It is a great place, very comfortable -- and easy to maintain.
I grew up in Eugene, Oregon but graduated from Oregon State in Corvallis. I was a high school teacher for 12 years.  Part of my teaching years were in Australia.  Very fond memories of living and traveling in Australia.  (My son was born in Australia.)
I work full time for Polk County in Dallas, Oregon.  I am a case manager for individuals with intellectual/development disabilities and I also license all of the adult foster homes in Polk County.
I enjoy skiing, working in my yard, going to movies, going to concerts, and spending time with my family.  I am also an avid NASCAR fan and football fan (college and professional.)
Hosting individuals in my home has been a rewarding experience.  I enjoy entertaining, meeting new and interesting people.  I want individuals staying at my home to have a restful, enjoyable, and comfortable experience.
Life motto;  Work hard, have fun, and be nice.

Other things to note
Parking is best done on the street directly in front of the house. I have never experienced

name: Century House Doug Fir Room
description:
Century House is just a few blocks from downtown, Bush Park, the Capitol, Willamette University, and Amtrak. Double bed, brand new private bathroom, kitchenette, two sitting rooms, with fireplace. Hi-speed internet. Park-like back yard with fire pit. Bicycles (plus gear, maps) for rent. Anytime coffee/tea/treats. Complimentary homemade morning pastry or fruit parfait. Full-course breakfast available for $10.00/person.

The space
Location, location, location.
Century House is just that. Built in 1912, it has been through flood and earthquake, but has been lovingly renovated to reflect the New England heritage of your hostess, Jean. Filled with modern amenities, and many non-fiction adventure books, games, a century-old baby grand piano. No TV, and no apologies :-).

Guest access
Coffee, tea, the cookie jar, the shady back yard, the common room, an extra sitting room, kitchenette, off-street parking, carriage house bicycle parking
neighborhood_overview: Walking/bicycling access to everything!
host_about:
Bicycling is my passion and my past-time, as well as my recipe for physical and emotional well-being.  Most recently, I have enjoyed “packing down” my bike with gear and heading down the road - for an overnight, or three, or three weeks.  This gives a whole new meaning to “bed and breakfast”.

When I’m not cycling, I’m usually busy cooking, cleaning, reading, sewing or watching the trees and flowers grow in my little forest; and, of course, accommodating the many fascinating guests who find their way to Century House from all corners of the globe.  My life is truly enriched by the diversity of perspectives and experiences that guests bring with them.

I confess, my favorite guests may be the children. With a full career of working in the field of early childhood, I never cease to be wowed by the uninhibited enthusiasm, curiosity, and resilience of the younger generation.  I am thrilled and dedicated to being a family-friendly business.

Another of my endeavors is the promotion/education of good nutrition.  I might be seen pedaling to a local farm to fill my packs with broccoli for the local food bank  - or, with fresh kale for a morning smoothie :-).  Don’t worry, there is still room for a brownie or an oatmeal cookie on the dessert tray.  After all, we need our dark chocolate, and our oatmeal, right?

Our home is in the quaint historic Fairmount Hills Neighborhood. This loft is great for business travelers, couples, and solo adventurers. We are close to Downtown, Bush Park, Salem Hospital, Willamette University, and Convention Center. We are also a great home base for exploring wineries and other communities. Our neighborhood is a safe place to walk and explore and our property has security cameras to enhance your safety.

The space
The studio is a quiet, private retreat above the garage, with all the necessities for a comfortable stay. The kitchen is equipped with fridge, microwave, hotplate, toaster and electric kettle.

We will get you started with homemade granola and sometimes a baked treat. Complimentary tea and coffee are provided along with a long list of restaurant recommendations.

The queen size, pillow top mattress is made up with luxury linens.

Guests are welcome to use the back patio and feel free to stroll thr
neighborhood_overview: Safe, quiet community, historic neighborhood. The studio is a few blocks from the Salem Art Fair, a short walk to eateries, museums, library, parks, Salem Hospital, Willamette University and the Capitol. This is wine country and we will be happy to share our favorites for you to visit.
host_about: We are an active couple that loves our home, neighborhood and surrounding area. We love the solitude of hiking and the warmth of an evening surrounded by family and friends.

name: Downtown Salem Loft in Salem Oregon
description:
As it has always been, the safety and security of our guests remains our highest priority. We take great pride in maintaining the highest standards of cleanliness and hygiene. I myself have personally provided direct patient care for over 39 years. In response to the coronavirus, we have taken additional measures developed in consultation with global and local public health authorities (including the WHO and CDC) to make our cleaning and hygiene protocols even more rigorous. Adults only please!

The space
Our teams are receiving ongoing briefings and enhanced operating protocols.
We have increased the frequency of cleaning our public areas (including lobbies, door handles, etc.) and have continued the use of hospital-grade disinfectant.
We have increased the deployment of antibacterial hand sanitizers.
We have even made personal take home antibacterial hand sanitizers for your purse or travel bag.Salem Oregon City Center New York style loft located
neighborhood_overview:
This loft is located 4 city blocks from the Oregon State Capitol. 5 city blocks from Willamette University and Halle Ford Museum. 2 blocks from the Salem Convention Center. 1 block from Riverfront park and the Willamette River. Front door opens to downtown boutique shops and restaurants. Full service mall, Salem Center, offers 65 National and local brands stores. There is a Cinema with 7 theaters that offers food and alcohol at your theater seat. We are 10 blocks from Salem Hospital and birthing center. We are 11 blocks from historical Bush Park, gardens and art barn next to Deepwood historical mansion.

Parks

Riverfront Park is a 23-acre park located in downtown Salem along the Willamette River connects to Wallace Marine Park which has 114.45 acres park that is the home of one of the best sports facilities in the Northwest and has miles of walking, jogging and biking paths. A $10 Million foot bridge is currently under construction and will open access to 800 a
host_about:
My name is Angela Jones, I grew up and have lived in Salem for the majority of my life. It is my home and I am so excited to share it with visitors! I have twin boys Max and Sam, who I am currently using my vacation rentals income to help put them both through college! My boys are my world, and I am proud of both of them. 
I am also an Arbonne Independent Consultant. Arbonne provides pure, safe and beneficial health and beauty products. Our products are made for those that don't want to use harsh chemicals and want true results in their health and their looks! 

As I got closer to having to start paying for my boys college, I decided to launch my vacation rental business with my Downtown Salem Loft. a 2400 sq ft "New York Style Loft" Apartment in the oldest historical building in downtown Salem.  I quickly realized this was my nitch, I was great at hosting guests and providing beautiful, affordable lodging in our Capitol City and Greater Willamette Valley and so it began. My vacation rental company is SalemStays. Currently I have 7 vacation rentals in Salem, 1 In Independence Oregon towards the coast and wine country and 1 in Stayton Oregon on the trail to Silver Falls State park and the Oregon Gardens! I love the hospitality business and supplying guests with beautiful, comfortable, and usable spaces to stay in for a much more reasonable price than staying in a hotel. 

I love to get to know all my guests and to make new connections. I hope you stay with me if you ever come to Salem OR or the Greater Willamette Valley.

name: Single room in Comfort Home
description:
Comfort Home was initially established for traveling medical professionals for Salem Health where I am the Clinical Excellence Coordinator. I provide discounts to RNs and other disciplines. I also rent to diverse guests and have enjoyed learning from everyone I've met. This home is perfect for sharing as I live in one section, the rooms are on the opposite side and our common space is perfect for everyone. I look forward to interacting should you be interested in making a request.

The space
Two rental rooms share a very large full bathroom with both tub and shower. One room has a private half bathroom. Guests share the grand room with living, dining and kitchen surrounding a three-sided gas fireplace. Guest can use home gym, backyard with hot tub and barbecue. The kitchen is designed for cooking and will share small amounts of condiments, spices and other items used for cooking. My space is on opposite side of house, upstairs and private.

Sel
neighborhood_overview:
Well established high end neighborhood with very friendly neighbors. Located on a cul-de-sac with adequate parking and little traffic so it is very quiet. Feels like a mountain resort due to the large and dense oak and pine trees. Back yard opens into quiet and beautiful neighborhood park.

10 minutes from I-5
Sunnyslope Shopping Center is a short walk from my home and has a wonderful grocery store (Roth's), U.S. Bank, restaurants, frozen yogurt shop, hair and nail salon, and more. Also within walking distance is a Walgreens, post office, gift shop and bakery. 4 miles from downtown Salem. Blocks from gas station.
host_about: I have lived in this home 21 years and have truly made it comfortable to both me and my guests.  The house is perfectly designed to accommodate guests as we built the 2-story extension that I live in upstairs which provides privacy for both myself and my guests.  My guests and I commonly share the downstairs which includes the kitchen, dining and living room, gym and back yard where there is a hot tub.

name: WittsPad
description:
The Edgewater District is the history of West Salem. Conveniently located on the edge of downtown Salem, you are within walking/biking distance from local eateries, the river, Audubon, coffee shop, tap-house, bookstore, mini-free libraries & more!

The space
There are 2 rooms available in this historical 1920's Craftsman. Beginning at the top, the attic offers a cozy studio-like atmosphere with a bookcase dividing the bedroom area from the private living room. The sofa in the living room pulls out to sleep 2 more guests, quite comfortably, on a memory foam mattress topper. The room is equipped with it's own portable air-conditioner/heating unit (and remote) for your preferred comfort. See photos of this listing by searching "WittsPad - Attic", or, find it under our listing profile.

The bedroom on the main floor sleeps 2 and boasts plenty of natural light. This room is adjacent to the shared bathroom and the common-area living room. Doors have a l
neighborhood_overview:
We are so close to a variety of options for recreation and enjoyment.

If you enjoy reading, there are several mini-free libraries in our immediate neighborhood & throughout Salem. We have a stash of books available for you to use as your "swap" with any of the inventory in the mini's. Or, if you want to get lost in our local new/used bookstore, "Reader's Guide", it's only blocks away :)

Also just 3 blocks away is a small but lovely Audobon Reserve where you can birdwatch, or, just stroll through and enjoy the nature trails.

Enjoy biking? Bring your own distance bike, or, use one of our "everyday" bikes to explore the nearby Willamette Valley Scenic Bikeway.

Walking/Running opportunities are just outside the door, when you jump on the greenway of Edgewater Park and head toward Riverfront Park, Wallace Marine Park, or, Minto Island Brown Park. There is a lovely walking bridge nearby to cross the Willamette River by foot or bike.

name: Spacious Suite w/ Private Sauna and AC in City
description:
Beautiful, large private Suite, w/ own key entry. Sparkling clean, upscale comfortable, you'll feel pampered right away.

15% discount for 3 day stay, 20% weekly, plus early and late booking discount!

Bedroom with en-suite and private sauna, living room, kitchenette. Clutter-free space with garden patio and BBQ. Convenient West Salem location, close to downtown and Willamette U., Salem Hospital, wineries, shops and parks.


Fully licensed and compliant with City of Salem codes.

The space
An actual guest review: "Fantastic place to stay. Beautiful part of Salem and the house was nicer than advertised. You can't go wrong."

Enjoy privacy in a beautiful and comfortable space with large master bedroom, private large living room including big screen TV and "kitchenette," which includes a microwave, mini-fridge, Keurig coffee machine and bar sink (there is no stove.) There is also a new Infrared CharBroil BBQ on th
neighborhood_overview: Explore wineries, waterfalls and the spectacular Oregon coast from your lovely and quiet West Salem location.  The Suite is within walking distance of shops and restaurants.  Only 2 miles to Capitol, Willamette University and downtown area.  Lots of trees and parks in neighborhood.  Beautiful hiking opportunities abound including "Silver Falls" which boasts 10 glorious waterfalls and miles of hiking trails.  Willamette Valley wineries including "Wine Spectator" top 100 picks will delight you.  Dozens of fabulous wineries in Salem and even more a short drive away.  The beach is only 45 minutes away.  One hour from Portland and airport.
host_about:
We love the Pacific Northwest!  Beautiful trees, parks, wineries and cultural activities abound.  Our new retreat/apartment will amaze you.  It's 770 sq ft. of gorgeous, quiet space and is an incredible value.  House hunting?  Visiting faculty?  This is the perfect home for you.

We are former long-term residents of Santa Cruz, California and never thought we could love anyplace as much--but we found out we love Salem and the Pacific Northwest even more!  We are voracious readers, faith and family are very important to us and we love to cook, entertain and visit wineries.  

We have a very large house because we have 5 grown children who we hope will visit--but our kids have very busy lives all over the country--In the meantime, we'd love to share our home with you.

name: Stylish, Private, Urban Guest House
description:
Enjoy our renovated, private guest house close to downtown Salem. We are on the city bicycle route in a historic, tree-lined neighborhood. Relaxing outdoor space and fully fenced yard. Note: The City of Salem requires a 9% Occupancy Tax, which is included in our nightly rate.

The space
The guest house is renovated with reclaimed wood used throughout. There is a small kitchenette with a sink, mini-fridge and small microwave. We encourage guests to visit the local eateries and not to "cook" in the space. However, you can heat leftovers or items in the microwave. We do not provide pots, pans and cooking items for this reason. There is air conditioning (and heat, of course), and an additional heater in the bathroom. There is an outdoor space for lounging when the weather is nice and a portico entry if it is raining, so you can remove wet gear. The yard is fully fenced and secure if you bring your pet. We also provide locally crafted items such as soaps and coffee.
neighborhood_overview: We are on the city bicycle route in a historic, tree-lined neighborhood. Walk to the Salem Farmer’s Market, Broadway Coffee House, McMenamins Boon's Treasury, and more. We are also a mile from downtown and a short drive to Willamette University.
host_about: Robert and I are avid campers and enjoy living in the Pacific Northwest. Although we love to travel, it is hard to leave the area as there are so many beautiful places to enjoy. We have a grown son and are dog lovers, love coffee, books, and always a great conversation around a camp fire. I am also a Realtor in Salem, so if you have any questions or needs, just let me know how I can help!

name: Spacious home near downtown Salem
description:
This charming 1927 home has been completely remodeled. The Willamette
River runs behind the homes across the street and the centrally located house is a one mile walk or bus ride to downtown.

The space
This is a lovely older home that has been completely remodeled. It is
surrounded by big leaf maple trees and the Willamette River runs behind the
houses across the street. There is a bedroom with a full sized bed and a
couch that folds out to a queen sized bed.

Guest access
You have access to the entire first floor. You have a private locked entrance
to your apartment. There is a full kitchen and laundry, a living room, dining
room and bedroom.

Other things to note
This property is licensed by the City of Salem
17-116988-L1
neighborhood_overview:
The proximity to the river is a great part of this neighborhood as are the large trees. Riverfront park and the carousal and West Salem Park are about a one mile walk from the house as is downtown Salem. The Broadway
district with an Independent theatre, coffee shops, restaurants and a wine
bar is a little less than a mile away. There is a rail line about 4 blocks from the house. Although it is not a main line, trains do pass through about twice a night and blow their whistle. Earplugs are provided.
host_about:
I am a retired psychotherapist.  It has been a labor of love to restore this lovely old house.  I love the outdoors and often hike, camp or kayak. I also enjoy meeting new people.  
Traveling is my passion and I have visited many countries and have enjoyed my stays in air b and b's.  Volunteerism is another passion and I hope to volunteer in Central America soon. There is some awesome energy in this house and I believe that more people will bring more good energy.

name: Immaculate home with Central AC in SE Salem
description:
Our Single Family one level air-conditioned home is easily accessible and conveniently located. Minutes away from City Center, State Capital, Eateries, Shopping, easy access to I-5, Enchanted Theme Park and Wineries. You are welcome to our home away from your home.

The space
Our guests have access to the entire house including a fully furnished kitchen, a laundry room which is fitted with washer, dryer and laundry supplies. This home has central air condition. Back deck has a gas grill with seating for 6.

Guest access
Guests have access to the entire house

Other things to note
Long term guests are welcome however any excessive use of utilities during guests stay may attract a surcharge.
neighborhood_overview: Our property is at a quiet neighborhood and we love our neighbors. We expect our guests to demonstrate respect towards our neighbors during their stay.
host_about: My wife and I have lived in the Northwest for over 20 years. We have two beautiful kids. We enjoy the outdoors and traveling to new places. name: Century House Cedar Room with lots of space, light
description:
The "Cedar Room" is a large, bright room with ensuite bathroom. Named for the 80-ft Cedar tree outside your window. Room includes a queen bed, dresser, lunch table and chairs, a small desk and chair, and a loveseat sofa. Shower, toilet, and sink are ensuite. Just across the hall are a sitting/reading/play/eating area, and a kitchenette with fridge, microwave, coffee/tea maker, dishes, utensils, condiments, etc. And, Century House is a museum of quilts.

The space
Bicycles and bike shop available for repairs, locked storage, rentals available. This is a great area for cycling!

Guest access

neighborhood_overview: Century House is walking distance to the State Capitol, Willamette University, Amtrak, and downtown. Enjoy gardens, historic homes, museums, restaurants, etc.
host_about:
Bicycling is my passion and my past-time, as well as my recipe for physical and emotional well-being.  Most recently, I have enjoyed “packing down” my bike with gear and heading down the road - for an overnight, or three, or three weeks.  This gives a whole new meaning to “bed and breakfast”.

When I’m not cycling, I’m usually busy cooking, cleaning, reading, sewing or watching the trees and flowers grow in my little forest; and, of course, accommodating the many fascinating guests who find their way to Century House from all corners of the globe.  My life is truly enriched by the diversity of perspectives and experiences that guests bring with them.

I confess, my favorite guests may be the children. With a full career of working in the field of early childhood, I never cease to be wowed by the uninhibited enthusiasm, curiosity, and resilience of the younger generation.  I am thrilled and dedicated to being a family-friendly business.

Another of my endeavors is the promotion/education of good nutrition.  I might be seen pedaling to a local farm to fill my packs with broccoli for the local food bank  - or, with fresh kale for a morning smoothie :-).  Don’t worry, there is still room for a brownie or an oatmeal cookie on the dessert tray.  After all, we need our dark chocolate, and our oatmeal, right?

The space
Our South Salem home is situated just outside the Salem city limits. The ground floor of this large house is all yours with over 1200 square feet of interior space. Come and go as you please through a separate private entrance.

Our property features pretty flower gardens, a large berry patch (in the summer, when berries are available, you can pick fresh blackberries or raspberries )! There's lots of room to kick back and relax.

- downtown Salem is 7 miles away

host_about:
Tom and I are originally from the Portland area and have lived in Salem for over 40 years. We raised our three sons here and now enjoy the quiet, natural setting full of hummingbirds, woodpeckers and deer. This place is like our own private park. 

We've got loads of flowers here. Over the years, Tom has planted apple and cherry trees, a plum tree, a fig tree, rhubarb, herbs and tomatoes, and a big berry patch full of blackberries, raspberries, blueberries, strawberries and currants. We like to call it "Tom's Berry Farm" but it isn't really a farm - though we sometimes joke that we could probably open up a roadside stand with all the produce.

Family is the most important thing to us and we enjoy spending time with our kids and grand kids. Other interests include cooking, reading, salmon fishing and volunteering for local charities like the Marion County Food Bank and Assistance League.

Our youngest son introduced us to Airbnb and we're excited for the opportunity to meet new people and share our peaceful home.

neighborhood_overview:
My home is located on a quiet street close to food, fuel and shopping. Salem is expanding with new restaurants and coffee shops: Rafn's and Archive are two of my favorites. But don't forget Kim Huong (Vietnamese), Wild Pear (Northwest cuisine), Ritter's (pizza + vegetarian) and Word of Mouth (the breakfast spot).

Bush Park and the Waterfront Park offer trails, playgrounds, and grass space - great for individuals and families.

Looking to explore outside of Salem? Head an hour south to Corvallis, home of the Oregon State Beavers, Eugene, home of the Oregon Ducks, or an hour North to Portland, foodie paradise and more.
host_about:
Hi!

Five years ago, the travel bug hit me, and I spent six months in Thailand, before venturing throughout the United States and then spending another three months in Thailand, Cambodia and Malaysia. I grew up on Air Force bases in Alaska, California, Florida, Washington, Oregon and the Philippine Islands.

I want to open up my home so that others can experience an authentic travel experience while visiting Oregon, a truly beautiful state, if I do say so myself!  Salem is the capitol of Oregon and approximately 45 miles south of our beloved Portland and an hour from our stunning coast.

I am happy to answer any of your questions or share any tips about the area; please do not hesitate to reach out to me. 

And thank you for looking at my listing.

Victoria

description:
Enjoy beautiful Willamette Valley Wine Country in this renovated one-bedroom apartment in a quiet South Salem neighborhood. Featuring a private entrance, fireplace, Sleep Number bed & air conditioning. Business ready, and close to Willamette, Corban and Western Oregon Universities, with shopping and restaurants nearby. Enjoy historic downtown Salem (a 10-minute drive), wine tasting at local wineries, or write that next great novel while you sit by the fire. Sunnyslope Retreat awaits you!

The space
Sunnyslope Retreat is a private apartment on the lower level of our home in the quiet South Salem Sunnyslope neighborhood, and is perfect for 1 or 2 adults (no children please). The entrance is at the rear of the house, with access down the left-side driveway.

Newly renovated (summer 2017), the 685 sq. ft. apartment has a large living area with comfortable furniture, 42" flat screen TV, Streaming RokuTV (access Netflix, Hulu, HBO, etc.), ceiling fans and
neighborhood_overview:
We are 10 minutes from I-5, off the Kuebler exit.
Close by, the Sunnyslope Shopping Center is a short walk from our home and has a wonderful grocery store (Roth's), U.S. Bank, laundromat, restaurants, frozen yogurt shop, hair and nail salon, and more. Also within walking distance is a Walgreens, post office, gift shop and bakery.

Downtown Salem is a 10-minute drive and has much to offer in the way of restaurants, coffee shops and shopping. Of special interest is Riverfront Park, whose two pedestrian bridges link it to West Salem and to Minto-Brown Island Park, which spreads out over 1,200 acres of lush, open and wooded areas. Willamette University is 4 miles away and just east of downtown. Corban University is 6 miles to the east.

Salem is located in the verdant Willamette Valley, famous for its wineries and farms. We are just over an hour from the coast and a couple hours from the mountains.
host_about:

They have 3 sons, one daugher in-law and 2 grandchildren. Family is a priority and their home is filled with rich memories of raising their family in Salem.

name: Historic & Charming Salem Home w/Mill Creek Views!
description:
Experience the stunning scenery and rich history of the Willamette Valley with a trip to this updated 19th-century vacation rental. The historic home is located in a quiet neighborhood within walking distance to the State Capitol and downtown Salem. Enjoy the sounds of the serene Mill Creek rushing by while you wine, dine, and grill on the patio. Head into town to tour museums and parks, visit one of the area’s many wineries, or bring the kids to top attractions like the Enchanted Forest!

The space
1,600 Sq Ft | Creekside Location | Dog Friendly w/ Fee | Furnished Patio | Sports/Gear Storage

Originally constructed in 1898, the renovated 'Daniel S. Yoder House' is on the National Registry of Historic Homes and boasts a seamless fusion of old-world sophistication and modern elegance, equipped with every amenity you need to feel at home!

Master Bedroom: King Bed | Bedroom 2: Queen Bed | Upstairs Den: Queen Futon | Downstairs Den: Queen Sleeper
neighborhood_overview:
DOWNTOWN: Oregon State Capitol (1.2 miles), Bush’s Pasture Park (1.3 miles), Gilbert House Children’s Museum (1.7 miles), Riverfront City Park (1.9 miles)
ATTRACTIONS: Enchanted Forest (9.0 miles), The Oregon Garden (13.7 miles), Evergreen Aviation & Space Museum (24.5 miles)
OUTDOORS: Mill Creek (walking distance), Minto-Brown Island Park (4.1 miles), Croisan Creek Trail (5.7 miles), Walsh's Landing Trailhead (6.7 miles)
WINERIES: Honeywood Winery (1.2 miles), Redhawk Vineyard & Winery (5.8 miles), Eola Hills (9.0 miles), Ankeny Vineyard (10.9 miles)
AIRPORT: Portland International Airport (58.5 miles)

name: Large Salem Townhome Close to Wineries & Parks!
description:
Experience the beauty and serenity of the Pacific Northwest from the comfort of 'Salem's R&R Home,' a 3-bedroom, 1.5-bath vacation rental townhome in Southeast Salem. Not only does this 1,425-square-foot home's elegant decor create a remarkably cozy ambiance, its proximity to the area's hottest attractions makes it truly one-of-a-kind. After days spent touring wineries, exploring parks, and perusing markets, you'll look forward to watching the sunset from the comfort of your manicured backyard.

The space
Master Bedroom: King Bed | Bedroom 2: Queen Bed | Bedroom 3: 2 Twin Beds

As you lounge in the living room, you'll be overwhelmed by the calming effect the room has on you. Boasting a plush couch, flat-screen satellite TV, and large windows, the room will truly feel like a private sanctuary. Beat the heat and stay cool, as you relax in this home's brand new quiet air-conditioning system.

When stomachs start to rumble, head into the fully eq
neighborhood_overview:
Boasting old-time charm, beautiful seasonal scenery, and several flowing waterways, Salem has something for everyone! Head 6 minutes down the road to Riverfront City Park and embrace the fun family atmosphere. Home to a handmade carousel, a footbridge, and more, this 23-acre park is both fun and beautiful.

Channel your inner sommelier by touring some of Willamette Valley's acclaimed wineries, or enjoy all the excitement surrounding Bush's Pasture Park, the location of the Salem Art Festival and Soap Box Derby. Alternatively, Oregon State Fairgrounds, a 185-acre venue, is home to many annual events, concerts, and other entertainment.

Enjoy the warm weather by exploring the top-notch outdoor markets that sit less than a mile from the property. Operating between Spring and Fall, these markets offer arts, crafts, and fresh local produce for incredibly low prices.

Don't feel like cooking? Take a quick walk to Word of Mouth Bistro, named Salem's restaurant

name: Century House Maple Suite
description:
Two bedrooms, a large completely refurbished master bath, a well-furnished kitchenette, and two common areas for eating, playing, working, reading, etc. Large queen room with lots of light, table/chairs, rocker, desk, and its own heating/cooling; and quiet corner room with double bed, easy chair, desk. Outside are dozens of shady places to relax, even in the rain. Your reservation includes a significant morning "snack". A full breakfast can be added for $10 per person with advance notice.

The space
Enjoy a large collection of handmade quilts, and a large collection of adventure stories related to bicycling and mountain climbing. Also, find numerous amenities for young children. Television is NOT one of them :-).
host_about:
Bicycling is my passion and my past-time, as well as my recipe for physical and emotional well-being.  Most recently, I have enjoyed “packing down” my bike with gear and heading down the road - for an overnight, or three, or three weeks.  This gives a whole new meaning to “bed and breakfast”.

When I’m not cycling, I’m usually busy cooking, cleaning, reading, sewing or watching the trees and flowers grow in my little forest; and, of course, accommodating the many fascinating guests who find their way to Century House from all corners of the globe.  My life is truly enriched by the diversity of perspectives and experiences that guests bring with them.

I confess, my favorite guests may be the children. With a full career of working in the field of early childhood, I never cease to be wowed by the uninhibited enthusiasm, curiosity, and resilience of the younger generation.  I am thrilled and dedicated to being a family-friendly business.

Another of my endeavors is the promotion/education of good nutrition.  I might be seen pedaling to a local farm to fill my packs with broccoli for the local food bank  - or, with fresh kale for a morning smoothie :-).  Don’t worry, there is still room for a brownie or an oatmeal cookie on the dessert tray.  After all, we need our dark chocolate, and our oatmeal, right?

name: Minto-Brown Island Bunkhouse Retreat  Salem Oregon
description:
The Bunkhouse retreat is located in the north ear of the 1,200 acres of lush, natural open and wooded area known as Minto-Brown Island Park. Walk, jog, or bike along 19 mile of hard and soft trail through native timber a grassy meadows. Enjoy fishing spots, a paddle boat area, and paved bikeways. The bunkhouse retreat nestled adjacent to Minto-Brown is proudly owned by a founding Salem family who history of the beautiful grounds and skilled landscape architecture dates back to the 19 hundreds.

The space
In 1857, Isaac "Whiskey"Brown established his home on what came to be know as Brown's Island, near the west bank of the Willamette River. Here the colorful and untidy Brown raised livestock, farm produce and tobacco. In 1867, John Minto purchased and cleared land on an island near the east bank, turning it into productive farmland, it would later come to be the named Minto Island. Today this beautiful place is a tranquil wildlife sanctuary! We are a working farm w
neighborhood_overview: Downtown Salem is less then 1/2 mile away! Which feels unreal when your out at the retreat. You can walk to Downtown from the park along the Willamette River walking trails. The Fairmount Neighborhood where the governors mansion is across the road on the hill. Tons of restaurants and coffee shops if you need a City break, but you come to get away and enjoy nature? The Bunkhouse has it all!
host_about:
My name is Angela Jones, I grew up and have lived in Salem for the majority of my life. It is my home and I am so excited to share it with visitors! I have twin boys Max and Sam, who I am currently using my vacation rentals income to help put them both through college! My boys are my world, and I am proud of both of them. 
I am also an Arbonne Independent Consultant. Arbonne provides pure, safe and beneficial health and beauty products. Our products are made for those that don't want to use harsh chemicals and want true results in their health and their looks!

description:
Charming, centrally located house built in 1910. High ceilings, original wood floors with one bedroom, full kitchen and a relaxing living room. Enjoy a cup of coffee on the front porch and watch the squirrels scurry about the majestic oak trees in this older neighborhood.
A five minute drive to Interstate 5, Willamette University, Oregon State Capital, Oregon Fairgrounds, wineries and historic downtown Salem.
There is a lovely neighborhood park a half block away for a nice evening walk as well.

The space
This is a 628 square foot house with a full kitchen, bedroom, bathroom and living area. The front porch is a peaceful spot to sip a cup of freshly brewed coffee and enjoy the majestic oak trees that line the street.

My hope is to create a restful and comfortable space for you to relax and recharge. Fee
neighborhood_overview:

Occasionally you may hear laundry being done in the adjacent laundry room but that is usually only in the day when I am cleaning the unit.
The backyard is shared space with the other unit. You are welcome to access the back yard through the gate in the front yard.

name: The Bunkhouse
description:
Located close to Englewood Park, the Bunkhouse is a unique, cabin-like dwelling.

Some say smaller than a tiny house, The Bunkhouse still has all the necessities for living: *dry toilet (google Loveable Loo for dry toilet information)
* mini kitchen - cold water in jugs, mini fridge, induction hot plate, toaster oven, hot water from dispenser or electric kettle, all necessary utensils
* elevated twin futon bed
* easy chair and TV tray for a table
* a view into the tall trees

The space
It's amazing what little space some of us actually need to be comfortable. At a cozy 8x8 feet, The Bunkhouse is a place to see that for yourself. It's a precious little space full of original art, good books, a view into the tall trees, and all the basics for a uniquely comfortable stay in Salem.

Other things to note
The bunkhouse has a dry toilet, meaning it does not flush but uses sawdust instead. Please google Loveable Loo

host_about:
My name is Angela Jones, I grew up and have lived in Salem for the majority of my life. It is my home and I am so excited to share it with visitors! I have twin boys Max and Sam, who I am currently using my vacation rentals income to help put them both through college! My boys are my world, and I am proud of both of them. 
I am also an Arbonne Independent Consultant. Arbonne provides pure, safe and beneficial health and beauty products. Our products are made for those that don't want to use harsh chemicals and want true results in their health and their looks! 

As I got closer to having to start paying for my boys college, I decided to launch my vacation rental business with my Downtown Salem Loft. a 2400 sq ft "New York Style Loft" Apartment in the oldest historical building in downtown Salem.  I quickly realized this was my nitch, I was great at hosting guests and providing beautiful, affordable lodging in our Capitol City and Greater Willamette Valley and so it began. My vacation rental company is SalemStays. Currently I have 7 vacation rentals in Salem, 1 In Independence Oregon towards the coast and wine country and 1 in Stayton Oregon on the trail to Silver Falls State park and the Oregon Gardens! I love the hospitality business and supplying guests with beautiful, comfortable, and usable spaces to stay in for a much more reasonable price than staying in a hotel. 

I love to get to know all my guests and to make new connections. I hope you stay with me if you ever come to Salem OR or the Greater Willamette Valley.

WHERE’S WALDO WOOD CABIN

The
neighborhood_overview: If you want to stay within close walking distance, maybe you don’t have a car, try Venti’s, The French Press, ACME, for restaurants, Roths and LIfe Source for groceries, and Aunt Bee’s House for vintage finds. Bush Park is close for a run or walk. Once you walk up to High Street there are sidewalks everywhere, making it a great walkable area. If you bring your bikes, let the host know and she will give you a key to the shed to keep your bikes secure.  The neighborhood is quiet, friendly and safe. Neighbors look out for each other. It’s the perfect house for getting ready to get married, for honeymooning, for a professional who needs a quiet sanctuary, or as a base camp to explore the Pacific NorthWest. Portland is a little over an hour away as is the Pacific Ocean. Hike Silver Falls, or take the Amtrak train which has a station within 2 miles and has free parking. Go to Seattle for a day or two and then come back to your Salem base camp, The Where’s Waldo Wood Cabin.
host_about:
My name is Angela Jones, I grew up and have lived in Salem for the majority of my life. It is my home and I am so excited to share it with visitors! I have twin boys Max and Sam, who I am currently using my vacation rentals income to help put them both through college! My boys are my world, and I am proud of both of them. 
I am also an Arbonne Independent Consultant. Arbonne provides pure, safe and beneficial health and beauty products. Our products are made for those that don't want to use harsh chemicals and want true results in their health and their looks!

neighborhood_overview:
I love my neighborhood because it is so close to everything you need. It is walking distance from Five Guys, Taco Bell, McDonalds, Pietro's Pizza, and many others.

The Willamette Town Center Mall with Regal Theater, Best Buy, Hobby Lobby and Red Robbins are all a few short minutes drive away.

It is a quick drive right downtown. Where you have riverfront park. I really enjoy grabbing a drink at Isaac's Coffee, Gov Cup or Broadway Coffee and going for a stroll. Broadway has a fireplace and amazing outdoor seating.

I love renting bikes with Zagster ($3 an hour!!!) and biking from downtown, through river front park, across the bike bridge into Minto Brown Island park. Worth it!

How far away is your AirBnB from...

- Salem Hospital, 3.2 miles
- Riverfront Park, 3.2 miles
- Market st. i5 exit, .5 miles
- Downtown, 2.8 miles
- Taco Bell, .5 miles
- Walgreens, .6 miles
- Bush Park, 3.3 miles
host_about:
I have traveled to 17 countries: Spain, England, Nepal, Thailand, Cambodia, Singapore, Mexico, Canada, Honduras, Costa Rica and Nicaragua. Oh and Scotland, South Africa, Mozambique, Oman and UAE. 

I love experiencing new things and meeting new people of the world. I learned Spanish when I lived in Mexico.

Lately I have been getting into loose leaf green tea.
Podcasts: Reply All, Heavy Weight, Another Kingdom (fiction)
TV: The Good Place, Schitt's Creek, The Office (forever and ever)
